cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as boundary detection, semantic segmentation, and object proposal generation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with image processing, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
